reviews.review_text:
Nevilles! Thanx tony, Sounded again like an east coast crowd, though rightfully quieter than the previous night.
Reasonably good audience recording, 3 stars.  Bob is way out front in the mix again.  Jerry's guitar did not need hiding, his playing was fine.  Just wondering?  I do like when bob is clear like these shows, seems later in the '80s he would get lost in the sound.
First set highlights, Row Jimmy 2nd tune!  A raucous Big River, and Sugaree, Jack Straw to end the set.  I always prefer Jack Straw as a set closer, more intense jamming (Syracuse '84) though some of the last jam in this one seems a tad forced.
Second set had a Box opener, still relatively new.  The Crazy Fingers and Estimated feature some great work by bob, real great sounds, particularly the Estimated, where he also screams like madman at the end.  The segment with the Nevilles was a great touch.  This was the penultimate version of handjive (only six performed) and leads into a rare two show in a row Aiko.  The Stella starts from a break, another rarity in the later years and is very emotional.  Set ending Sugar Mags are never a bad thing.  The Midnight Hour is a bit raggedy, as are most Bob versions. 
If you are not a completist I would recommend the second set.
Each set fits onto one disc, so don't break up set 2 when you burn.  Peace
